      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "409cuR-sJ3F9"
      },
      "source": [
        "Raw term frequencies: *tf (t,d)*â€”the number of times a term t occurs in a document *d*"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "KVHKTNchJ3F-"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Task 3: Word relevancy using term frequency-inverse document frequency"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "n2fUGlOcJ3F-"
      },
      "source": [
        "$$\\text{tf-idf}(t,d)=\\text{tf (t,d)}\\times \\text{idf}(t,d)$$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "v38DDmqjJ3F-"
      },
      "source": [
        "$$\\text{idf}(t,d) = \\text{log}\\frac{n_d}{1+\\text{df}(d, t)},$$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "NtiI3afpJ3F-"
      },
      "source": [
        "where $n_d$ is the total number of documents, and df(d, t) is the number of documents d that contain the term t."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Tf is term frequency idf is inverse document frequency"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "R6NKfpb2Zb92"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "oCNAgz88J3F_",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "outputId": "e4fc0740-22cb-4545-f6f2-1eacebab80da"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "[[0.   0.43 0.   0.56 0.56 0.   0.43 0.   0.  ]\n",
            " [0.   0.43 0.   0.   0.   0.56 0.43 0.   0.56]\n",
            " [0.5  0.45 0.5  0.19 0.19 0.19 0.3  0.25 0.19]]\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfTransformer\n",
        "np.set_printoptions(precision=2)\n",
        "\n",
        "tfidf = TfidfTransformer(use_idf=True, norm='l2', smooth_idf=True)\n",
        "print(tfidf.fit_transform(bag).toarray())"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Core Idea of tfidf ---> it converts your text data to numeric values and also weight the values appropriately according to the number of times they occur in your corpus of text data."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "y5NroZtxcuXO"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "GVfyiw8XJ3GC"
      },
      "source": [
        "The equations for the idf and tf-idf that are implemented in scikit-learn are:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\text{idf} (t,d) = log\\frac{1 + n_d}{1 + \\text{df}(d, t)}$$\n",
        "The tf-idf equation that is implemented in scikit-learn is as follows:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\text{tf-idf}(t,d) = \\text{tf}(t,d) \\times (\\text{idf}(t,d)+1)$$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "cZrUPz5kJ3GD"
      },
      "source": [
